titleStmt.title: An ordinance of the Lords and Commons assembled in Parliament, for reliefe of the subiect, who have been prejudiced by stopping and discontinuing of writs of error which said writs are to be sealed with the Great Seale of England, ordeined and estabished by both Houses of Parliament.
titleStmt.author: England and Wales. Parliament.

notesStmt.note: Order to print dated: 15 May 1644, and signed: H. Elsinge Cler. Parl. D. Com.
